article.description: Florida A&M tops FIU in OT 93-88
article.headline: Florida A&M tops FIU in OT 93-88
article.linkText: Florida A&M tops FIU in OT 93-88
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- Jamari Bradshaw's 3-pointer forced overtime, and he scored five of Florida A&M's 12 points in the extra session, to lead the Rattlers over Florida International 93-87 Thursday night. Bradshaw finished with 26 points and nine rebounds. FIU (8-7) led by six with 54 seconds left in the game. But A&M forced OT as FIU made just 5 of 10 free throws in that time and Bradshaw's 3 with 8 seconds left tied it up. He then made a jumper and 3 free throws in OT while FIU went 1 of 7 from the floor. The Rattlers (4-10) got 20 points from Jamie Adams while Trey Kellum added 17. Dennis Mavin led FIU with 24 points, including 16 of 21 on free throws. FIU shot 49 percent from the floor, but was just 3 of 13 from beyond the arc. Tymell Murphy had 17 points while Cody Mann added 16 points.
